{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1689].
  {panel}

I just realized that everyone shares the same view of draft edits!!!

What?  That means that you can't tinker with a plan without changing everyone's view of the plan.

I suggest that draft edits need to be scoped to an individual.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1688].
  {panel}

Many of our projects use different technologies and not everyone on the dev team has the same skills. 

We do something like scrumban and estimate by story points on the story (and convert to hours in Portfolio). 

There doesn't seem to be a way to say "This issue requires these skills" and then have Portfolio only consider those team members who have those skills.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1686].
  {panel}

This is a request to have a pre-defined list of groupers (Themes or Components) that carry across JIRA and Portfolio without dual documentation. And whatever is chosen, it should be allowed to be incorporated into hierarchy in Portfolio and as both a filter and column option in Portfolio.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1685].
  {panel}

As a Product Manager I want to see the sum of the values of child issues custom fields in JIRA Portfolio Scope Grid so that I could have more information about Initiatives.

This is very important for us, since other native fields already have this (Story Points for example). We added budget custom field and we want to see the sum of it on Portfolio.

For example: Epics have a budget field, and we want to see the sum of it on the Initiative and other top Hierarchy issues. The same thing that happens to Story Point field for example.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1681].
  {panel}

We have restricted modify access to Portfolio to users who have attended training to ensure that there are no big data problems caused by users who don't know what they are doing (especially as there is no audit log in Portfolio). 

However, this means they are now the only users who can set values in the Parent Link and Team fields in JIRA, which is causing a lot of confusion for our users as the fields are visible to all users. 

We would like users who do not have permission to modify Portfolio plans to be able to set the values in these fields.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1680].
  {panel}

Currently we can define a default estimate for each level of the issue hierarchy (example: epic vs story). It would be nice if we could configure a default estimate for issue types (example: task vs bug).

On our team, the level of effort needed to fix a bug is generally less than the level of effort needed to complete a task -- it would be nice to set a default estimate for this use case.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1677].
  {panel}

As a product owner who manages multiple products, I'd like the ability to import themes created in one portfolio plan into a new portfolio plan either from a master list of themes created for an entire organization or by a team or by department. I would like the ability to choose which themes I import into a new plan so if a specific theme wouldn't be used, I could choose to only import the specific themes out of the master list that I want.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1676].
  {panel}

I need a reporting capability in order to report to my Steerco. I would like to extract the porfolio reports into a PPT deck for my monthly reports to Steerco.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1672].
  {panel}

Hi, I can understand why the Team field is locked to stop someone deleting it, but it restricts how it can be used.
Firstly, I can't setup any value, unless I go to Portfolio and set them up first.  Common practise when you have multiple teams is to have a Teams common field which you then assign Stories to.  I can't do this with the Portfolio field.
Secondly in an enterprise there will be a lot of Teams, and I don't really want the entire list available to all project.  I usually setup a field context applied to projects which then has options on which are the available teams who can work on those projects.  That way there is a restricted list available in each project and its very difficult to choose an incorrect team.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1670].
  {panel}

I've created a plan with a bunch of existing tasks. Most of the tasks were not assigned to releases when I created the plan. It would take ~18 months to complete all the existing work. I'm most concerned with sorting out our priorities for the next three months. It's frustrating that the only way to view the next three months on the timeline has the side-effect of hiding from the scope view those epics which Portfolio says I won't be touching in those three months. It makes it very hard to adjust the releases and dependencies for issues so that the plan tells my team what to work on first.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1667].
  {panel}

I want to filter on the Team in Jira but don't see that as a field.

