  {panel}

This would allow me to organize my Stories by Epic.  It would be sweeter if there was a way to drill down through initiatives, epics, stories then sub-tasks but I'll take the quick win of just being able to organize my stories by epic.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1665].
  {panel}

If there is a dependency between two stories you can see there is a dependency in the schedule view when viewing the epic level, but on clicking the epic the detail panel says there is no dependency. 

While technically this is true for the epic, it's very confusing for users as they are not able to see which issues actually have dependencies without going through each of the stories.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1662].
  {panel}

When viewing Stories in the timeline view, there is no visual indicator of each story's parent epic.

Sometimes stories names only make sense in the context of the epic.  Without a visual indicator of the parent epic, the story name makes no sense.

Request a visualization of the parent epics.  Maybe how stories can be grouped by team, you could group by epic.

